huh, interesting question that I suppose I can answer now that I'm not asleep and the thread is past bump limit.

auger frame sub-gunners rarely have anything bigger than 20-40mm autocannons at their disposal, so one managing to whittle down an enemy machine without assistance from the main pilot would be quite the event. i.e. that motherfucker would become a household name among sub-gunners, the kind of guy you use to batter people over the head. 'maybe if you watched your screens more, you'd be like X, he killed a battleframe with those things ya know'

as to how the kill would be credited, a sub-gunner is basically credited with a kill assist if he manages to assist the pilot with a kill by knocking out enemy optics or something like that. A gunner's job is keeping the smallfry away from the mech while the pilot tackles the bigger threats, so it's basically unheard of for them to really try and do anything more than assist their pilot with the main target. As for how the one-kill wonder would make an ace with a four-kill pilot, there may have to be new legislation surrounding that.
